                                        Pneumoconiosis is defined as a tissue reaction in the lungs that occurs by inhaling dust and accumulating in the lungs.
                                    </p>

                                    <h3>How is it caused?</h3>
                                    <p class="pera-bottom mb-30">
                                        In general, when the dust is absorbed through the respiratory tract, most of the dust is discharged to the outside through the ciliary movements of the bronchi, but some dust cannot escape and accumulates in the lungs, causing inflammation, and fibrosis occurs due to a continuous inflammatory reaction. Not all types of dust cause pneumoconiosis, there are special types of dust that cause pneumoconiosis. There are also a variety of actions that can cause pneumoconiosis.

                                    </p>
